## M22.1(1/8): resource-producing temporary cloned with `+` is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 39: `+(*Cell(...))` bumps the refcount on a
## fresh Rc but the original strong handle never gets installed
## into a binding; its M20e guard is missing. The clone keeps the
## allocation alive while the original strong slot leaks.

sub main()
  c = +(*Cell(value: 0))    # error: anonymous *Cell temporary leaks
  print(c.get())
